haughty /ˈhɔːtɪ/

1. ADJ You use haughty to describe someone's behaviour or appearance when you disapprove of the fact that they seem to be very proud and to think that they are better than other people. 傲慢的 [usu ADJ n] [表不满] 

例： He spoke in a haughty tone. 他说起话来口气傲慢。 

2. haughtily ADV 

例： Toni looked at him rather haughtily. 托尼非常傲慢地看着他。

